Package: worldfoundry-dev
Version: 1.0.0
Architecture: all
Maintainer: World Foundry <packages@worldfoundry.org>
Section: metapackages
Priority: optional
Depends: worldfoundry-engine-build-deps,
 worldfoundry-blender,
 worldfoundry-retro-tools,
 task,
 gnupg,
 ca-certificates,
 software-properties-common
Recommends: code,
 worldfoundry-android-dev
Suggests: claude-code
Homepage: https://docs.worldfoundry.org/
Description: complete World Foundry game-development environment
 The top-level metapackage — installs everything required for World
 Foundry game development on Ubuntu-family 26.04: the engine build
 toolchain, Blender 4.2 with the WF addon, retro-porting tools, and
 the task runner.
 .
 Android cross-compilation tooling and Claude Code CLI are
 Recommends/Suggests respectively — install worldfoundry-android-dev
 explicitly if you need Android.
 .
 This is Phase 1 of the Foundry Linux distro plan. Phase 0 (the
 curl-bash installer at https://worldfoundry.org/install.sh) covers
 the same package set but composes it inline; this metapackage
 collapses that to a single apt-install.
